title: SoftBank sues social media startup it invested in, alleging it faked user numbers
description: Buzzy social media startup IRL launched in April 2021 and was seemingly "one of the fastest growing social media apps for Generation Z," the complaint alleges.

title: Apple shares fall most since September 2022 after third-quarter earnings report
description: Apple's earnings beat soft expectations on both profit and revenue, but overall sales declined 1% as iPhone, iPad and Mac sales flagged.

title: JPMorgan backs off recession call even with 'very elevated' risks
description: Economists at the country's largest bank bailed on their recession call, joining a growing chorus that now thinks a contraction is no longer inevitable.

title: 'Barbie' is less than $100 million away from a billion-dollar box office heading into third weekend
description: "Barbie" is expected to hit a billion-dollar benchmark before Monday, making Greta Gerwig the first solo female director to have a film cross the mark.

title: Facing lawsuit from Musk, nonprofit head says he won't stop exposing Twitter's problems
description: The head of the Center for Countering Digital Hate said his nonprofit will continue researching alleged hate speech on Twitter despite a lawsuit from Musk.

title: Amazon stock rockets 11%, on pace for best day since November after blowout quarter
description: Analysts cheered stabilizing AWS growth, improving retail margins and progress on cutting costs.

title: Jailed Putin critic Alexei Navalny handed 19 more years in prison
description: Navalny, one of Russian President Vladimir Putin's most vocal critics, was already serving two prison sentences.

title: Apple shares slide after it reports decreased revenue for iPhone and other hardware
description: Shares of Apple were down Friday morning after the company reported lower year-over-year revenue for its flagship products in its third quarter.

title: Google is offering an on-campus hotel 'special' to help lure workers back to the office
description: The offer is part of the search giant's efforts to bring remote employees back to offices.

title: The U.S. economy added 187,000 jobs in July, fewer than expected
description: Nonfarm payrolls were expected to increase by 200,000 in July, according to the Dow Jones consensus estimate.

title: Apple, Samsung could be hit by India laptop and PC import restrictions
description: Laptops and tablets are among a handful of electronics that will require a license to be imported into India, according to a government notice.

title: South American countries gripped by record-breaking heat — in the middle of winter
description: Climatologist Maximiliano Herrera says South America's scorching winter heat represents one of the most "extreme events the world has ever seen."

title: No rate hikes or cuts — Commerzbank CFO says the European Central Bank has likely hit pause
description: The European Central Bank has likely pressed pause on its rate hiking cycle, the chief financial officer of Commerzbank told CNBC on Friday.

title: Huawei plots China smartphone revival with mobile operating system upgrade
description: Huawei launched its upgraded mobile operating system and an enhanced AI assistant on Friday.

title: How interest rates impact your money — from savings to mortgages
description: Interest rates may seem abstract, but they affect everyone. CNBC Make It examines the role they play in your finances.

title: Shipping giant Maersk beats expectations despite 72% profit plunge on falling container rates
description: Danish shipping giant Maersk on Friday reported a sharp fall in second-quarter earnings on the back of plunging container rates.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Amazon surges as Apple stumbles
description: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy's cost-cutting measures paid off handsomely. Meanwhile, Apple continues to struggle with dipping revenue.

title: Drought threatens major European river trade route with ripples across the continent
description: The river Rhine, an important trade route that runs through Germany, has become shallower at critical points meaning vessels sail with reduced loads.

title: Chinese property stocks surge after central bank vows more support for private businesses
description: Shares of Longfor Group and Country Garden Holdings were among the top gainers on the Hang Seng Index.

title: China lifts anti-dumping tariffs on Australian barley after three years, easing supply concerns
description: China was the indisputable top recipient of Ukrainian agricultural products — including about a quarter of outbound barley volume, according to United Nations data Thursday.

title: Apple's most profitable line of business is making up for some hardware struggles
description: In the June quarter, Apple's services business grew over 8%, and the company says the current period is poised to show even faster expansion.

title: South Korean defense stocks power ahead as overseas interest grows for weapon systems
description: South Korea has benefited from increased global military expenditure, according to Morgan Stanley, citing Stockholm International Peace Research Institute.

title: Automakers promote advanced tech to compete in China — the world's top EV market
description: China is the world's largest EV market with 5.9 million units sold in 2022, capturing 59% of EVs sold globally, according to Canalys.

title: Japan is Asia's most expensive location to send expats — here are the other top spots
description: Globally, Japan ranked second while the U.K. came up on top as the most expensive location to send expatriates, according to ECA International.

title: Amazon CEO Jassy's cost cuts deliver investors biggest profit beat since 2020
description: Amazon reported earnings that blew past estimates on Thursday, showing just how far the company's cost cuts have gone to bolster profitability.

title: A new luxury hotel is opening near Singapore — but you'll need a boat to reach it
description: ONE°15 Marina Nirup Island joins other private islands that have opened in Indonesia's Riau Island. A Westin hotel is scheduled to open in late 2024.
